      "message": "it looks like that all operations on |mCount| except this one are performed inside a lock/unlock block, i.e. can be done with relaxed order. If tryWrite() / tryRead() are properly used, size() should not appear in the hot traces anymore. This means you can get rid of the atomic variable, and just use a lock here, this will make the code much more readable.",
